{"name":"sc_task","description":"Tracks tasks related to service catalog items.","summary":"Sure! Here's a summary of the `sc_task` object for the ServiceNow application:\n\nThe `sc_task` object in ServiceNow is used to manage tasks within the Service Catalog. It represents individual tasks that are part of a larger service catalog request. Here are some key points about the `sc_task` object:\n\n1. **Purpose**: It is designed to track and manage the progress of tasks that are part of a service catalog request. Each task can have its own set of attributes and workflow.\n\n2. **Relationships**: The `sc_task` object is typically related to the `sc_request` object, which represents the overall service catalog request. Each `sc_request` can have multiple `sc_task` records associated with it.\n\n3. **Attributes**: Some common attributes of the `sc_task` object include:\n   - **Task Number**: A unique identifier for the task.\n   - **Short Description**: A brief description of the task.\n   - **State**: The current state of the task (e.g., Open, In Progress, Closed).\n   - **Assigned To**: The user or group responsible for completing the task.\n   - **Due Date**: The deadline for completing the task.\n   - **Parent Request**: The `sc_request` record to which the task belongs.\n\n4. **Workflow**: Tasks can be part of a workflow that defines the sequence of actions and approvals required to complete the service catalog request.\n\n5. **Use Cases**: The `sc_task` object is used in various scenarios, such as tracking the progress of IT service requests, managing approvals, and ensuring that all necessary steps are completed before a service is delivered.\n\nBy effectively managing `sc_task` records, organizations can ensure that service catalog requests are processed efficiently and that all required tasks are completed in a timely manner.","attributes":[{"name":"parent","type":"reference"},{"name":"made_sla","type":"boolean"},{"name":"watch_list","type":"glide_list"},{"name":